<item>
            <title>[OAK-1177] Node#isModified returns true if node has non-readable child</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-1177</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;issue reported by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tripod&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tripod&quot;&gt;tripod&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=&quot;http://markmail.org/message/uxnl26chtqmrimoi&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://markmail.org/message/uxnl26chtqmrimoi&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i created a test where a node contains access control content which restricts access to a given child node -&amp;gt; the parent node is marked as modified for the test session that is not allowed to see the child.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12679002">OAK-1177</key>
            <summary>Node#isModified returns true if node has non-readable child</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
