                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13821240" author="anchela" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 11:38:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;test cases illustrating the issue committed at revision 1541477.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821245" author="anchela" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 11:48:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;quickly debugged one of the test cases: the problem seems indeed to be caused by MutableTree#isModified() as &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mduerig&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mduerig&quot;&gt;mduerig&lt;/a&gt; suspected.&lt;br/&gt;
this method compares the original base (NodeState obtained from the NodeStore) with the nodeBuilder, which is a SecureNodeBuilder. This obviously will find differences if there are child nodes or properties that are not accessible... it might even wrongly return true if there are hidden items that are filtered out by one or the other.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821247" author="anchela" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 11:51:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i would suggest that we compare the original base with the non-secured node builder as in this case there is no need to verify the accessibility of the child items.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;... or simply delegate the call to NodeBuilder#isModified&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821355" author="anchela" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 13:56:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1541521: delegated evaluation to NodeBuilder#isModified&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13828751" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2013 10:30:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;bulk close for the 0.11 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
